---------------------------------------------------------
DYNAPHOPY 1.3
---------------------------------------------------------
Program to calculate crystal anharmonic frequency shifts
and phonon linewidths from molecular dynamics simulations
performed with VASP code using PHONOPY harmonic eigenvalues.

---------------------------------------------------------
Installation instructions
---------------------------------------------------------
1. Requirements
Python 2.7 or higher
Phonopy (http://phonopy.sourceforge.net)
Matplotlib
Scipy
h5py

2. Download the source code and place it in the installation directory

3. Run setup.py script to install
python setup.py install --user

---------------------------------------------------------
Executing the program
---------------------------------------------------------
1) Command line method
./dynaphopy input_file vasp_MD_OUTCAR [Options]
execute ./dynaphopy -h for detailed description of available options

2) Interactive mode
Use -i option from command line method and follow the instructions
./dynaphopy input_file vasp_MD_OUTCAR -i

3) Scripting method (as a module)
Create/edit script like input.py and execute it
The comments in the script makes it (hopefully) self explained.
    Example: input.py

Input files for several materials can be found in Example directory
More information at: http://abelcarreras.github.io/DynaPhoPy

